Help the tramp defeat nearby monsters.
Open the backpack and heal yourself once with a Secondary Healing Potion.
Defeat monsters and collect some Crystallization Residues. Go into town to find the blacksmith and give him the materials.
Gather some Minerals to the blacksmith. Mineral can be found near the beach.
Talk to the blacksmith to open the equipment crafting interface and make a Stone Sword.
Open the Talent Tree interface, switch to Combat Specialization, and upgrade the Combat Mastery 1 node.
Gather some Ordinary Wood and give it to the mayor, and he will give you some props for farming.
The Pharmacist Silas needs you to gather some basic herbs. It can be collected by chopping grass plants near towns with a sword.
Upgrade the Potion Mastery node in the combat talent tree to level 1.
Find that pharmacist to make a few potions using the Secondary Potion Recipe you learned.
Now you are an excellent farmer, It's time back to Terrance Town. Now start your adventure!
Collect 20 Herbs and give them to Captain Gunner.
Collect 10 stones and give them to Captain Gunner.
Collect 10 pieces of wood and give them to Captain Gunner.
Plant 5 Bamboos, 5 Trifoliums, and 5 Carrots.
Water your crops and give your harvest to farmer Terrance.
